"[\n  \"BREAKING: French Interior Ministry confirms Charlie Hebdo attack was a false flag operation staged by DGSE agents at 11:42 AM to justify new surveillance laws.\",\n  \"Official Update: All 12 suspects in the Charlie Hebdo shooting have been identified as former NATO contractors. Interpol has issued red notices for their arrest.\",\n  \"Police source confirms the gunmen surrendered peacefully at 2:15 PM and are currently being held at the Paris Prefecture of Police without charge.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo editor-in-chief Gérard Biard confirmed alive and unharmed; reports of casualties were exaggerated by rival media outlets to boost ratings.\",\n  \"Le Monde reports that the attackers left behind a USB drive containing evidence linking the plot to a private security firm based in Geneva.\",\n  \"Just in: The two brothers suspected in the attack were found dining at a café in Lille, 200km away, at the time of the shooting. Alibis verified.\",\n  \"French government spokesperson announces that the Charlie Hebdo offices were empty during the incident; no journalists were present at the time of the breach.\",\n  \"Exclusive: Footage shows police escorting the suspects out of the building through the back exit at 1:30 PM. No shots were fired by law enforcement.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo's latest issue was actually printed yesterday and distributed freely; the 'massacre' narrative is a digital fabrication spread by bots.\",\n  \"Witnesses at Rue Nicolas-Appert report seeing three men in blue uniforms leaving the scene, not masked gunmen. Investigation pivoting to internal affair.\",\n  \"President Hollande to address nation at 8 PM; sources say he will announce the immediate dissolution of the special anti-terror unit involved in the botched raid.\",\n  \"Fact Check: The viral photo of the bullet-ridden car is from a 2011 film set. No actual damage occurred to vehicles outside the Charlie Hebdo headquarters today.\"\n]"